<paragraph id="8B8B0743161AFFF5B59EE0266A4DCE67" blockId="12.[160,1155,769,934]" box="[160,276,769,795]" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">
<emphasis id="B940DB51161AFFF5B59EE0266A4DCE67" bold="true" box="[160,276,769,795]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B0743161AFFF5B59EE001684BCEDA" blockId="12.[160,1155,769,934]" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">
<emphasis id="B940DB51161AFFF5B59EE0016BB4CE42" box="[160,237,806,830]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">Worker</emphasis>
. Antennal scapes when laid back from their insertions surpassing posterior margin of head by more than half of its length; propodeal spines short, acute and curved; petiole bituberculate; pronotum with a single pair of long hairs; body smooth and shining black, antennae, tibiae and tarsi yellowish.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
