<subSubSection id="C32E54C8161AFFF5B59EE6696958C8AC" pageId="12" pageNumber="328" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8B0743161AFFF5B59EE6696A2EC814" blockId="12.[160,1155,1358,1488]" box="[160,375,1358,1384]" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">
<emphasis id="B940DB51161AFFF5B59EE6696A2EC814" bold="true" box="[160,375,1358,1384]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">Geographic range</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B0743161AFFF5B59EE6546958C8AC" blockId="12.[160,1155,1358,1488]" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">
This species has a wide distribution in central Asia but on the Arabian Peninsula it has been recorded only in 
<collectingCountry id="F32347D3161AFFF5B497E6B16AB4C8D2" box="[425,493,1430,1454]" name="Oman" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">Oman</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F32347D3161AFFF5B715E6B169D9C8D2" box="[555,640,1430,1454]" name="Yemen" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">Socotra</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA57AB2161AFFF5B7AEE6B16839C8D2" author="Collingwood CA" box="[656,864,1430,1454]" pageId="12" pageNumber="328" pagination="230 - 302" refId="ref18149" refString="Collingwood CA. 1985. Hymenoptera: fam. Formicidae of Saudi Arabia. Fauna Saudi Arabia. 7: 230 - 302." type="journal article" year="1985">Collingwood 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA57AB2161AFFF5B651E6B16B8EC8AC" author="Collingwood CA &amp; Agosti D" pageId="12" pageNumber="328" pagination="300 - 385" refId="ref18173" refString="Collingwood CA, Agosti D. 1996. Formicidae (Insecta: Hymenoptera) of Saudi Arabia (part 2). Fauna of Saudi Arabia. 15: 300 - 385." type="journal article" year="1996">Collingwood and Agosti 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA57AB2161AFFF5B5DBE69F6AADC8AC" author="Collingwood CA &amp; Pohl H &amp; Guesten R &amp; Wranik W &amp; Van Harten A" box="[229,500,1464,1488]" pageId="12" pageNumber="328" pagination="473 - 495" refId="ref18239" refString="Collingwood CA, Pohl H, Guesten R, Wranik W, Van Harten A. 2004. The ants (Insecta: Hymenoptera: Formicidae) of the Socotra Archipelago. Fauna of Arabia. 20: 473 - 495." type="journal article" year="2004">Collingwood et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32E54C8161AFFF5B59EE6DB694CCB6A" box="[160,533,1532,1558]" pageId="12" pageNumber="328" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B8B0743161AFFF5B59EE6DB694CCB6A" blockId="12.[160,1156,1532,1696]" box="[160,533,1532,1558]" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">
<emphasis id="B940DB51161AFFF5B59EE6DB694CCB6A" bold="true" box="[160,533,1532,1558]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">Ecological and biological notes</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32E54C8161AFFF7B59EE507691ECCC0" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="330" pageId="12" pageNumber="328" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8B0743161AFFF7B59EE507691ECCC0" blockId="12.[160,1156,1532,1696]" lastBlockId="14.[160,1156,142,444]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="330" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0161AFFF5B59EE5076ADECB44" baseAuthorityName="Kuznetsov-Ugamsky" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[160,391,1568,1592]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lepisiota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="328" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinisquama">
<emphasis id="B940DB51161AFFF5B59EE5076ADECB44" box="[160,391,1568,1592]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">Lepisiota spinisquama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected from dry soil under a date palm tree by sifting. A colony was found nesting under a stone in Dixam 
<collectingRegion id="49F0C9A1161AFFF5B748E5646991CB27" box="[630,712,1603,1627]" country="Nigeria" name="Plateau" pageId="12" pageNumber="328">Plateau</collectingRegion>
. A nest was collected from under a dead palm tree where the soil had a high degree of humidity and was rich in organic material. Another colony was found under a stone where exoskeletons of minor workers of a yellow 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC01618FFF7B59EE3A96A16CDDA" box="[160,335,142,166]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Camponotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B940DB511618FFF7B59EE3A96A7FCDDA" box="[160,294,142,166]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="330">Camponotus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
were present. Workers were observed foraging on the trunk of 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC01618FFF7B11DE3A96A6ECDB5" authority="Flueck." authorityName="Flueck." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Burseraceae" genus="Boswellia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="14" pageNumber="330" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carteri">
<emphasis id="B940DB511618FFF7B11DE3A96BBBCDB5" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="330">Boswellia carteri</emphasis>
Flueck.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC01618FFF7B478E3966A92CDB5" box="[326,459,177,201]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Burseraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="14" pageNumber="330" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Burseraceae</taxonomicName>
) where many worker of 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC01618FFF7B7D8E3966F57CDB5" authority="(Forel)" baseAuthorityName="Forel" box="[742,1038,177,201]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Trichomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mayri">
<emphasis id="B940DB511618FFF7B7D8E3966899CDB5" box="[742,960,177,201]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="330">Trichomyrmex mayri</emphasis>
(Forel)
</taxonomicName>
were also found at the trunk base and the soil was dry. Several mealybugs (
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC01618FFF7B66FE3F3689FCD90" box="[849,966,212,236]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Hemiptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC01618FFF7B6F1E3F36F27CD90" box="[975,1150,212,236]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pseudococcidae</taxonomicName>
) were observed under the bark of the tree. The species was also found nesting under a stone with several dead tenebrionid beetles and a species of the family 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC01618FFF7B6B9E23E68ACCC4D" authorityName="Schilling" authorityYear="1829" box="[903,1013,281,305]" class="Insecta" family="Lygaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lygaeidae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC01618FFF7B13AE23E6F22CC4D" box="[1028,1147,281,305]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Hemiptera</taxonomicName>
). Several workers of 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC01618FFF7B44FE21B6957CC28" baseAuthorityName="Kuznetsov-Ugamsky" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[369,526,316,340]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Lepisiota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinisquama">
<emphasis id="B940DB511618FFF7B44FE21B6A25CC28" box="[369,380,316,340]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="330">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B940DB511618FFF7B4B4E21B6957CC28" box="[394,526,316,340]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="330">spinisquama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were foraging on ground where soil was sandy and dry. Several individuals were collected from a dry leaf litter by sifting. A nest was located in a relatively moist, compact clay soil under a stone. Previous observations indicate that this species apparently prefers dry habitats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
